# Naming Conventions

- Follow Google C++ style as the baseline.
- All function names use lowercase with underscores (`snake_case`).
- Production file names use lowercase letters only and do not use underscores.
- Unit test file names must be `<corresponding_file_name>_test.cpp`.
- All header files use `#pragma once` only; do not use include guards.
- Apply naming consistently to new files and refactors.

## Examples

```cpp
// Good
int read_events();
bool open_output(const std::string& path);
```

```text
// Good file names
inputdevice.cpp
filesystem.h
evdevlinux.cpp
inputdevice_test.cpp
argparser_test.cpp
```

